com.tapjoy
Class TapjoyConnectFlag

java.lang.Object
  com.tapjoy.TapjoyConnectFlag

public class TapjoyConnectFlag
extends java.lang.Object

Flags used in TapjoyConnect.requestTapjoyConnect(android.content.Context, java.lang.String, java.lang.String) to define special startup options.

These flags can also be defined in the meta-data tags in AndroidManifest.xml. They must be put within the tag and the format is:

SHA_2_UDID

public static final java.lang.String SHA_2_UDID
Sends the SHA2 hash of UDID/deviceID (IMEI/MEID/serial) in sha2_udid parameter instead of the udid parameter.
Use "true" as the flag value.
CAN ONLY BE USED IN THE ADVERTISER/CONNECT SDK.

Constant Field Values

STORE_NAME

public static final java.lang.String STORE_NAME
Sets the app to use a different market/app store other than Google Play. If not set, Google Play will be used.
Use the store name as the flag value.
